"{\n  \"correct\": \"no\",\n  \"explanation\": \"The DateFormatter in matplotlib expects the dates to be in the format that datestr2num returns, which is days since 0001-01-01 00:00:00 UTC, plus one. However, the DateFormatter is being set to format the dates as '%d/%m/%Y', which is not the format of the input to datestr2num. The datestr2num function is being used correctly to convert the dates to the correct format for matplotlib, but then the DateFormatter is being set to a different format.\",\n  \"patch\": \"13c13\\n<ax.xaxis.set_major_formatter(DateFormatter(\\\"%d/%m/%Y\\\"))\\n---\\n>ax.xaxis.set_major_formatter(DateFormatter(\\\"%m/%d/%Y\\\"))\\n\"\n}"